</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Sealed Air Corporation<br>2415&nbsp;Cascade Pointe Boulevard<br>Charlotte, North Carolina 28208</P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:36pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">April&nbsp;4, 2019 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Dear Fellow Stockholder: </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">It is my pleasure to invite you to attend the Annual Meeting of Stockholders of Sealed Air Corporation to be held on Thursday, May&nbsp;16, 2019, at
10:00 a.m., Eastern daylight time. This year&#146;s Annual Meeting will again be a &#147;virtual meeting&#148; conducted via live audio webcast. Each stockholder will be able to participate in the Annual Meeting by accessing a live webcast at
<I>www.virtualshareholdermeeting.com/SEE2019</I> and entering the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">16-digit</FONT> control number included on the stockholder&#146;s Notice of Internet Availability of Proxy Materials or proxy card. Stockholders will
also be able to vote their shares and submit questions via the Internet during the meeting by participating in the webcast. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">By conducting the
Annual Meeting via live audio webcast, we are embracing the latest technology to provide expanded access and improved communication for our stockholders. As we have learned, hosting a virtual meeting enables increased stockholder attendance and
participation from locations around the world. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">During the Annual Meeting, stockholders will be asked to elect the entire Board of Directors and to
ratify the appointment of Ernst&nbsp;&amp; Young LLP as our independent auditor for 2019. We also will be asking stockholders to approve, by an advisory vote, our 2018 executive compensation as disclosed in the Proxy Statement for the Annual
Meeting. These matters are important, and we urge you to vote in favor of the election of each of the director nominees, the ratification of the appointment of our independent auditor, and the approval of our 2018 executive compensation. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">We are again furnishing proxy materials to our stockholders over the Internet. This <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">e-proxy</FONT> process expedites
stockholders&#146; receipt of proxy materials, lowers our costs and reduces the environmental impact of the Annual Meeting. Today we sent to most of our stockholders a Notice of Internet Availability of Proxy Materials containing instructions on how
to access our Proxy Statement for the Annual Meeting and our 2018 Annual Report to Stockholders, as well as how to vote via the Internet. Other stockholders will receive copies of the Proxy Statement, a proxy card and the 2018 Annual Report by mail
or <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">e-mail.</FONT> </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">It is important that you vote your shares of common stock at the virtual meeting or by proxy,
regardless of the number of shares you own. You will find the instructions for voting on your Notice of Internet Availability of Proxy Materials or proxy card. We appreciate your prompt attention. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">The Board of Directors invites you to participate in the Annual Meeting so that management can discuss business trends with you, listen to your
suggestions and answer your questions. Thank you for your continuing support, and we look forward to joining you at Sealed Air&#146;s 2019 Annual Meeting. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Sincerely, </P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="justify">


<IMG SRC="g685314g58b00.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:4pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Edward (Ted) L. Doheny II </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify"><I>President and Chief Executive Officer </I></P>
</DIV></Center>

<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g685314g35x57.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Notice of Annual Meeting of Stockholders </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Sealed Air Corporation, a Delaware corporation (&#147;Sealed Air&#148;), will hold its Annual Meeting of Stockholders (the &#147;Annual Meeting&#148;)
on May&nbsp;16, 2019, at 10:00 a.m., Eastern daylight time. The Annual Meeting will again be conducted as a virtual meeting via live audio webcast. Each stockholder may participate in the Annual Meeting, including casting votes and submitting
questions, by accessing the live audio webcast at <I>www.virtualshareholdermeeting.com/SEE2019</I> and then using the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">16-digit</FONT> control number provided on the Notice of Internet Availability of Proxy Materials
or proxy card being delivered to the stockholder. Online <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">check-in</FONT> to the Annual Meeting webcast will begin at 9:45 a.m., Eastern daylight time, and stockholders are encouraged to allow ample time to log in to
the meeting webcast and test their computer audio system. There will be no physical location for the Annual Meeting. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">The purposes for the Annual
Meeting are to consider and vote upon: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">The Board of Directors has fixed the close of business on March&nbsp;18, 2019 as the record date for the determination of stockholders entitled to
notice of, and to vote at, the Annual Meeting. Sealed Air is making available or mailing its 2018 Annual Report to Stockholders to all stockholders of record as of the record date. Additional copies of the 2018 Annual Report are available upon
written request to the Corporate Secretary at Sealed Air Corporation, 2415 Cascade Pointe Boulevard, Charlotte, North Carolina 28208. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Because it is
important that as many stockholders as possible be represented at the Annual Meeting, stockholders should review the attached Proxy Statement promptly and carefully and then vote. A stockholder may vote by following the instructions for voting set
forth on the Notice of Internet Availability of Proxy Materials or proxy card. A stockholder who receives a paper copy of the proxy card by mail will also receive a postage-paid, addressed envelope that can be used to return the completed proxy
card. A stockholder who joins the Annual Meeting may vote electronically at the Annual Meeting. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Sealed Air will maintain a list of stockholders of
record as of the record date at Sealed Air&#146;s corporate headquarters, 2415 Cascade Pointe Boulevard, Charlotte, North Carolina, for a period of ten days prior to the Annual Meeting. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">On behalf of the Board of Directors, </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Angel S.
Willis </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Vice President, General Counsel and Secretary </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Charlotte, North
Carolina </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">April&nbsp;4, 2019 </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Proposal</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="justify"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>2. Ratification of Appointment of Independent Auditor for 2019
</B></FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">We are asking stockholders to ratify the Audit Committee&#146;s retention of Ernst&nbsp;&amp; Young LLP, an
independent registered public accounting firm, as our independent auditor to examine and report on our consolidated financial statements and the effectiveness of our internal control over financial reporting for the fiscal year ending
December&nbsp;31, 2019. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:30pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:12pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Proposal</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="justify"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>3. Approval of 2018 Executive Compensation on an Advisory Basis
</B></FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">We are asking for stockholder approval, on an advisory basis in accordance with Securities and Exchange Commission
rules, of the 2018 compensation of our &#147;named executive officers&#148; as disclosed under &#147;Executive Compensation&#148; in this Proxy Statement, including the disclosures set forth thereunder in &#147;&#151;Compensation Discussion and
Analysis&#148; and the compensation tables and related narrative discussion. </P>
</div><br clear="All"></div><br clear="All">

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right">3 </P>

</DIV></Center>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B><I>Key Features of Our Executive Compensation Program </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">The Compensation Committee believes that our executive compensation program follows best practices aligned to long-term stockholder interests, as
summarized below: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

Do</B></FONT></P></TD></TR>

of compensation in performance-based compensation</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="justify">


<IMG SRC="g685314g86q58.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle">Consistent&nbsp;with&nbsp;our&nbsp;goal&nbsp;of&nbsp;creating a performance-oriented environment, 65% of total direct compensation for CEO, and 55% of total direct compensation for other named executive officers, are
performance-based</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#dbeaeb" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.50em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" COLOR="#12737c">&#10003;</FONT>&#8194;&#8201;Pay for
performance based on goals for both annual and long-term awards</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="justify">


<IMG SRC="g685314g86q58.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle">Use multiple, balanced measures, including use of both absolute and relative measures for long-term awards</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.50em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" COLOR="#12737c">&#10003;</FONT>&#8194;&#8201;Balanced mix of
awards tied to annual and long-term performance</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="justify">


<IMG SRC="g685314g86q58.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle">For CEO, total direct compensation includes 16% in annual incentive award and 70% in long-term awards at target; for 2018, 70% of long-term awards for named executive officers were performance-based and 30% were
time-based</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#dbeaeb" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.50em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" COLOR="#12737c">&#10003;</FONT>&#8194;&#8201;Stock ownership
and retention policy</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="justify">


<IMG SRC="g685314g86q58.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle">Multiple of base salary must be held in common stock &#151; 6x for CEO, 3.5x for CFO and 3x for other Senior Vice Presidents; 100% of <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">after-tax</FONT> shares must be held until ownership goal is
met</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.50em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" COLOR="#12737c">&#10003;</FONT>&#8194;&#8201;Compensation
recoupment (clawback) policy</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="justify">


<IMG SRC="g685314g86q58.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle">Recovery of annual or long-term incentive compensation based on achievement of financial results that were subsequently restated due to error or misconduct, regardless of whether named executive officer was responsible for the
error or misconduct</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#dbeaeb" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">

compensation consultant</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="justify">


<IMG SRC="g685314g86q58.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">Compensation consultant (FW Cook) provides no other services to Sealed Air</TD></TR>

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">

<div style ="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000;BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000;BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000;BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000;MARGIN-LEFT:0px; MARGIN-RIGHT:0px;max-width:100%"><div style="width:97%; margin-top:1.5%; margin-left:1.5%; margin-right:-1.25%">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B><I>Key Elements of our Executive Compensation Program </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">The following table summarizes the main components of our executive compensation program for our named executive officers. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="26%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="37%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="33%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt" BGCOLOR="#12737c">
<TD HEIGHT="4" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="4" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="4" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#12737c" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Compensation Element</FONT></B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Description</FONT></B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Objectives</FONT></B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">Base Salary</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Fixed cash compensation</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Appropriate level of fixed compensation based on role and
duties</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Assist with recruitment and retention</P></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#dbeaeb" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">Annual Incentive</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Annual cash award if performance metrics are achieved</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Target
award based on a percentage of base salary</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Payouts from <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">0-200%</FONT> of target based on company and individual performance</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Certain executives eligible to elect all or a portion of award in form of
restricted stock award vesting over two years, with 25% enhancement; maximum 5 years participation; no new participants after 2018</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Reward executives for driving superior operating and financial
results over a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-year</FONT> timeframe</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Create a direct connection between business success and financial
reward</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">Long-Term Incentives</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Performance share units earned based on performance, typically
over three-year period with <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">0-200%</FONT> payout</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Time-vesting restricted stock or restricted stock units vesting annually over
three years</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Occasional awards of restricted stock or restricted stock units that vest at end
of three years of service</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Reward achievement of longer-term goals</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Create
direct connection between <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">longer-term</FONT> business success and financial reward</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Encourage retention</P></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#dbeaeb" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">Retirement Plans</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Standard plans generally offered to all salaried employees
based on location of services</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;No&nbsp;supplemental&nbsp;executive&nbsp;retirement plans</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Provide retirement income for participants</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Assist with
recruitment and retention</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">Deferred Compensation</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Elective, nonqualified deferred compensation plan for select
U.S. employees</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Permits deferral of salary and certain cash incentives</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;No Sealed
Air contributions are included</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Provide opportunity to save for retirement</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Assist with
recruitment and retention</P></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#dbeaeb" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">Post-Employment Benefits</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Executive Severance Plan provides competitive benefits in case
of involuntary termination; no single-trigger vesting of equity awards upon a change in control</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Mr.&nbsp;Doheny&nbsp;also&nbsp;has&nbsp;post-employment benefits under the terms
of his offer letter agreement</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Assure continuing performance of executives in face of
possible termination of employment without cause</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#12737c">&#149;</FONT>&#8194;&#8202;Assist with recruitment and retention</P></TD></TR>

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">Other Benefits</P></TD>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">6 </P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">

<div style ="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000;BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000;BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000;BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000;MARGIN-LEFT:0px; MARGIN-RIGHT:0px;max-width:100%"><div style="width:97%; margin-top:1.5%; margin-left:1.5%; margin-right:-1.25%">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Participation in the Virtual Annual Meeting </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">The Board of Directors considers the appropriate format of our annual meeting of stockholders on an annual basis. This year the Board again chose a
virtual meeting format for the Annual Meeting in an effort to facilitate stockholder attendance and participation by enabling stockholders to participate fully, and equally, from any location around the world, at no cost. The virtual meeting format
will allow our stockholders to engage with us at the Annual Meeting from any geographic location, using any convenient internet-connected&nbsp;devices, including smart phones and tablet, laptop or desktop computers. We will be able to engage with
all stockholders as opposed to just those who can afford to travel to an <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">in-person</FONT> meeting.&nbsp;The virtual format allows stockholders to submit questions and comments during the meeting. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">The live audio webcast of the Annual Meeting will be available for listening by the general public, but&nbsp;participation in the Annual Meeting,
including voting shares and submitting questions, will be limited to stockholders. To ensure they can participate, stockholders and proxyholders should visit <I>www.virtualshareholdermeeting.com/SEE2019</I> and enter the <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">16-digit</FONT> control number included on their Notice of Internet Availability of Proxy Materials or proxy card. If you wish to participate in the meeting and your shares are held in street name, you must obtain, from
the broker, bank or other organization that holds your shares, the information required, including a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">16-digit</FONT> control number, in order for you to be able to participate in, and vote at, the Annual Meeting.
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">If you have any questions or concerns regarding meeting access or procedures prior to the Annual Meeting, please call: <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">1-704-503-8841</FONT></FONT></FONT> or send emails to <I>investor.relations@sealedair.com</I>. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Stockholders can vote their shares and submit questions via the Internet during the Annual Meeting by accessing the annual meeting website at
<I>www.virtualshareholdermeeting.com/SEE2019</I>. We will answer any timely submitted questions on a matter to be voted on at the Annual Meeting before voting is closed on the matter. Following adjournment of the formal business of the Annual
Meeting, we will address appropriate general questions from stockholders regarding Sealed Air in the order in which the questions are received. All questions received during the Annual Meeting will be presented as submitted, uncensored and unedited,
except that we may omit certain personal details for data protection issues and we may edit profanity or other inappropriate language. If we receive substantially similar questions, we will group those questions together and provide a single
response to avoid repetition. Additional information regarding the submission of questions during the Annual Meeting can be found in our 2019 Rules of Conduct and Procedure, available at <I>www.virtualshareholdermeeting.com/SEE2019.</I> </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Online <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">check-in</FONT> to the Annual Meeting webcast will begin at 9:45&nbsp;a.m., Eastern daylight time, and you
should allow ample time to log in to the meeting webcast and test your computer audio system. During online <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">check-in</FONT> and continuing through the length of the Annual Meeting, we will have technicians standing
by to assist you with any technical difficulties you may have accessing the virtual meeting. If you encounter any difficulties accessing the Annual Meeting during the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">check-in</FONT> or at meeting time, you should
call <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">1-855-449-0991</FONT></FONT></FONT> (toll-free) or <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">1-720-378-5962</FONT></FONT></FONT> (toll line). </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">We have designed our virtual format to enhance, rather than constrain,
stockholder access, participation and communication. For example, stockholders will be able to communicate with us during the Annual Meeting so they can ask questions. An audio replay of the Annual Meeting will be made publicly available at
<I>http://ir.sealedair.com/presentations-events </I>and will remain publicly available for approximately one year. This audio replay will include each stockholder question addressed during the Annual Meeting. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">We are utilizing technology from Broadridge Financial Solutions, Inc., or Broadridge, the leading virtual meeting solution. The Broadridge platform is
expected to accommodate most, if not all, stockholders. Both we and Broadridge will test the platform technology before going &#147;live&#148; for the Annual Meeting. </P>
</div><br clear="All"></div><br clear="All">

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right">7 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B><I><A NAME="toc685314_2"></A>Questions and Answers about the Annual Meeting
</I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:14pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Q:</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="justify"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B></B><I>When and where will the Annual Meeting be held?</I> </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>A:</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="justify"><B></B>This year the Annual Meeting of Stockholders of Sealed Air Corporation, which we refer to below as the Annual
Meeting, will be held via live audio webcast at <I>www.virtualshareholdermeeting.com/SEE2019</I>, beginning at 10:00&nbsp;a.m., Eastern daylight time, on Thursday, May&nbsp;16, 2019. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">This year&#146;s annual meeting will again be a virtual meeting of stockholders conducted solely via live audio webcast. Each stockholder
may participate in the Annual Meeting, including casting votes and submitting questions during the Annual Meeting, by accessing a live webcast at <I>www.virtualshareholdermeeting.com/SEE2019</I> and then using the
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">16-digit</FONT> control number provided on the Notice of Internet Availability of Proxy Materials or proxy card being delivered to the stockholder. There will be no physical location for the Annual Meeting. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Online <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">check-in</FONT> to the Annual Meeting webcast will begin at 9:45&nbsp;a.m., Eastern daylight
time. We encourage you to allow ample time to log in to the meeting webcast and test your computer audio system. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

participation in the Annual Meeting, including voting shares and submitting questions, will be limited to stockholders. To ensure they can participate, stockholders and proxyholders should visit <I>www.virtualshareholdermeeting.com/SEE2019</I> and
enter the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">16-digit</FONT> control number included on their Notice of Internet Availability of Proxy Materials or proxy card. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>

printed set of proxy materials?</I> </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>A:</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="justify"><B></B>In accordance with rules and regulations adopted by the Securities and Exchange Commission, we are furnishing
the proxy materials to most stockholders by providing access via the Internet, instead of mailing printed copies. This <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">e-proxy</FONT> process expedites our stockholders&#146; receipt of proxy materials, lowers our
costs and reduces the environmental impact of the Annual Meeting. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">The Notice of Internet Availability of Proxy
Materials tells you how to access and review the proxy materials on the Internet and how to vote on the Internet. The Notice also provides instructions you may follow to request paper or <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">e-mailed</FONT> copies of our
proxy materials. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="justify"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><I>Are the proxy materials available via the Internet?</I> </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<I>http://ir.sealedair.com/shareholder-services/annual-meeting</I>. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>A:</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="justify"><B></B>Stockholders of record of our common stock at the close of business on March&nbsp;18, 2019, the record date,
will be entitled to vote at the Annual Meeting. A total of 155,752,407 shares of common stock were outstanding as of the record date. Each share outstanding on the record date will be entitled to one vote on each proposal. In addition, holders of
record of W.R. Grace&nbsp;&amp; Co. common stock issued prior to March&nbsp;31, 1998 and outstanding at the record date will have an aggregate of 1,686 votes on each proposal. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">As a result, a total of 155,754,093 votes will be eligible to be cast on each proposal at the Annual Meeting. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Q:</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="justify"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B></B><I>What is a stockholder of record?</I> </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>A:</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="justify"><B></B>A stockholder of record is a stockholder whose ownership of stock is reflected directly on the books and
records of our transfer agent, Broadridge. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Q:</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="justify"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B></B><I>What does it mean for a broker or other nominee to hold shares in &#147;street
name&#148;?</I> </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>A:</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="justify"><B></B>If you beneficially own shares held in an account with a broker, bank or similar organization, that
organization is the stockholder of record and is considered to hold those shares in &#147;street name.&#148; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">An
organization that holds your beneficially owned shares in street name will vote in accordance with the instructions you provide. If you do not provide the organization with specific voting instructions with respect to a proposal, under the rules of
the New York Stock Exchange the organization&#146;s authority to vote your shares will depend upon whether the proposal is considered a &#147;routine&#148; or <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-routine</FONT> matter. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">The organization generally may vote your beneficially owned shares on routine items for which you have not provided
voting instructions to the organization. The only routine matter expected to be voted on at the Annual Meeting is the ratification of the appointment of our independent auditor for 2019 (Proposal&nbsp;2). </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">The organization generally may not vote on <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-routine</FONT> matters, including
Proposals 1 and 3. Instead, it will inform the inspector of election that it does not have the authority to vote on those matters. This is referred to as a &#147;broker <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-vote.&#148;</FONT> </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right">9 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>

Meeting any proxies that are voted on any of the three proposals to be acted upon by the stockholders, including abstentions or proxies containing broker <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-votes.</FONT> </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

Annual Meeting as follows: </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

instructions printed on the Notice of Internet Availability of Proxy Materials and the proxy card. Internet voting is available 24 hours a day until 11:59 p.m., Eastern daylight time, on May&nbsp;15, 2019. You will be given the opportunity to

recorded properly. If you vote by telephone, you do not need to return a proxy card. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

card as a voting instruction card to provide voting instructions to Fidelity Management Trust Company, or Fidelity, the trustee for the 401(k) and Profit-Sharing Plan, for the shares of common stock allocated to your plan account or accounts.
Fidelity will vote your allocated shares in the plan in accordance with directions you provide by 11:59 p.m., Eastern daylight time, on May&nbsp;13, 2019. If you do not provide timely voting instructions to Fidelity, the terms of the plan provide
that Fidelity will vote your shares in the same proportion as shares it votes on behalf of participants who do provide timely voting instructions. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">10 </P>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Q:</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="justify"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B></B><I>Can I vote at the Annual Meeting?</I> </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>A:</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="justify"><B></B>If you are a stockholder of record, you generally will be able to vote during the Annual Meeting, whether or
not you previously voted. If your shares are held in street name, you must obtain, from the broker, bank or other organization that holds your shares, the information required, including a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">16-digit</FONT> control
number, in order for you to be able to participate in, and vote at, the Annual Meeting. If you hold shares through our 401(k) and Profit-Sharing Plan, you cannot vote those shares at the Annual Meeting. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Q:</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="justify"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B></B><I>Can I ask questions at the Annual Meeting?</I> </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>A:</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="justify"><B></B>You may submit questions via the Internet during the Annual Meeting by participating in the webcast at
<I>www.virtualshareholdermeeting.com/SEE2019</I>. We will answer any timely submitted questions on a matter to be voted on at the Annual Meeting before voting is closed on the matter. Following adjournment of the formal business of the Annual
Meeting, we will address appropriate general questions from stockholders regarding Sealed Air in the order in which the questions are received. All questions received during the Annual Meeting will be presented as submitted, uncensored and unedited,
except that we may omit certain personal details for data protection issues and we may edit profanity or other inappropriate language. If we receive substantially similar questions, we will group those questions together and provide a single
response to avoid repetition. Additional information regarding the submission of questions during the Annual Meeting can be found in our 2019 Rules of Conduct and Procedure, available at <I>www.virtualshareholdermeeting.com/SEE2019</I>.
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Q:</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="justify"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B></B><I>Why is the Annual Meeting being conducted as a virtual meeting?</I>
</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>A:</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="justify"><B></B>The Board of Directors considers the appropriate format of our annual meeting of stockholders on an annual
basis. This year the Board again chose a virtual meeting format for the Annual Meeting in an effort to facilitate stockholder attendance and participation by enabling stockholders to participate fully, and equally, from any location around the
world, at no cost. The virtual meeting format will allow our stockholders to engage with us at the Annual Meeting from any geographic location, using any convenient internet-connected devices, including smart phones and tablet, laptop or desktop
computers. We will be able to engage with all stockholders as opposed to just those who can afford to travel to an <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">in-person</FONT> meeting. The virtual format allows stockholders to submit questions and comments
during the meeting. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">We are utilizing technology from Broadridge Financial Solutions, Inc., or Broadridge, the
leading virtual meeting solution. The Broadridge platform is expected to accommodate most, if not all, stockholders. Both we and Broadridge will test the platform technology before going &#147;live&#148; for the Annual Meeting. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Q:</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="justify"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B></B><I>What should I do if I have questions about meeting access or procedures prior to the
Annual Meeting?</I> </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>A:</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="justify"><B></B>If you have any questions or concerns regarding meeting access or procedures prior to the Annual Meeting, you
should call <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">1-704-503-8841</FONT></FONT></FONT> or send emails to <I>investor.relations@sealedair.com</I>. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Q:</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="justify"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B></B><I>What should I do if, during <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">check-in</FONT> or the
meeting, I have technical difficulties or trouble accessing the virtual meeting website?</I> </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>A:</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="justify"><B></B>Online <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">check-in</FONT> to the Annual Meeting webcast will begin at 9:45 a.m.,
Eastern daylight time. You should allow ample time to log in to the meeting webcast and test your computer audio system. During online <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">check-in</FONT> and continuing through the length of the Annual Meeting, we will
have technicians standing by to assist you with any technical difficulties you may have accessing the </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right">11 </P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">If you are a beneficial owner of shares held in street name, you should contact your bank, broker or other nominee for instructions as to
whether, and how, you can change or revoke your proxy. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Q:</B></FONT></TD>

</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>A:</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="justify"><B></B>If you are a stockholder of record and you return a proxy card without giving specific voting instructions, the
Proxy Committee will vote your shares in the manner recommended by the Board of Directors on all three proposals presented in this Proxy Statement and as the Proxy Committee may determine in its discretion on any other matters properly presented for
a vote at the Annual Meeting. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">If you are a beneficial owner of shares held in street name and do not provide
specific voting instructions to the broker, bank or other organization that is the stockholder of record of your shares, the organization generally may vote on routine matters but not on <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-routine</FONT> matters.
The only routine matter expected to be voted on at the Annual Meeting is the ratification of the appointment of our independent auditor for 2019 (Proposal 2). If the organization does not receive instructions from you on how to vote your shares on
one or both of Proposals 1 and 3, your shares will be subject to a broker <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-vote</FONT> and no vote will be cast on those matters. See &#147;<I>Q. What does it mean for a broker or other nominee to hold shares in
&#145;street name&#146;?</I>&#148; above. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">12 </P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B><I><A NAME="toc685314_3"></A>Vote Required for Election or Approval
</I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:14pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Introduction </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">As of the record date, which is the close of business on March&nbsp;18, 2019, 155,752,407 shares of common stock were outstanding, each of which is
entitled to one vote at the Annual Meeting. In addition, holders of record of W.R. Grace&nbsp;&amp; Co. common stock issued prior to March&nbsp;31, 1998 and outstanding at the record date will have an aggregate of 1,686 votes on each proposal at the
Annual Meeting, which means there will be a total of 155,754,093 votes eligible to be cast at the Annual Meeting. Holders who are present virtually or represented by proxy and who hold shares representing a majority of the votes eligible to be cast
will constitute a quorum for the transaction of business at the Annual Meeting. For the purpose of determining a quorum, we will treat as present at the Annual Meeting any proxies that are voted on any matter to be acted upon by the stockholders, as
well as abstentions or any proxies containing broker <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-votes.</FONT> </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Proposal 1.&nbsp;&nbsp;Election of
Directors </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Each director will be elected by a vote of the majority of the votes cast with respect to that director, where a majority of
the votes cast means that the number of shares voted &#147;for&#148; a director must exceed the number of votes cast &#147;against&#148; the director. We will not count shares voted to &#147;abstain&#148; for the purpose of determining whether a
director is elected. Similarly, broker <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-votes</FONT> will not have any effect on the outcome of the election of directors since broker <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-votes</FONT> are not counted as
&#147;votes cast.&#148; </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Under our Certificate of Incorporation, our Bylaws and the Delaware General Corporation Law, a director holds office until
a successor is elected and qualified or until his or her earlier resignation or removal. Eight of the nine nominees currently serve as our directors. If any of the nominees who are currently in office is not elected at the Annual Meeting, then the
Bylaws provide that the director shall offer to resign from the Board of Directors. The Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee will make a recommendation to the Board whether to accept or reject the resignation, or whether other actions
should be taken. The Board will consider and act on the recommendation of the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee and publicly disclose its decision and the rationale behind it within ninety days from the date of the certification of the
election results. The director who offers his or her resignation will not participate in the decision of the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee or the Board. If the Board accepts such resignation, then the Board may fill the vacancy
resulting from that resignation or may reduce the number of directors that constitutes the entire Board so that no vacancy exists. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Proposal 2.&nbsp;&nbsp;Ratification of Appointment of Independent Auditor for 2019 </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">The ratification of Ernst&nbsp;&amp; Young LLP as our independent auditor for the year ending December&nbsp;31, 2019 requires the affirmative vote of a
majority of the votes entitled to be cast and present virtually or represented by proxy at the Annual Meeting. Abstentions will be deemed present and, therefore, will count as votes against this proposal. Because this proposal is considered a
routine matter, discretionary votes by brokers will be counted. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B>Proposal 3.&nbsp;&nbsp;Approval of 2018 Executive Compensation on an
Advisory Basis </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">The approval of the advisory vote to approve our 2018 executive compensation requires the affirmative vote of a majority
of the votes entitled to be cast and present virtually or represented by proxy at the Annual Meeting. Abstentions will count as votes against this proposal, since shares with respect to which the holder abstains will be deemed present and entitled
to vote. Broker <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-votes</FONT> will have no effect on the outcome of this proposal, since broker <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-votes</FONT> are not counted as &#147;votes cast.&#148; </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right">13 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><B><I><A NAME="toc685314_4"></A>Corporate Governance </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:14pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><I><A NAME="toc685314_5"></A>Corporate Governance Guidelines </I></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">The Board of Directors has adopted and operates under Corporate Governance Guidelines that reflect our current governance practices in accordance with
applicable statutory and regulatory requirements, including those of the Securities and Exchange Commission, or SEC, and the New York Stock Exchange, or NYSE. The Corporate Governance Guidelines are available on our website at
<I>www.sealedair.com.</I> </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><I><A NAME="toc685314_6"></A>Independence of Directors </I></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Under the Corporate Governance Guidelines and the requirements of the NYSE, the Board of Directors must consist of a majority of independent directors.
The Board annually reviews the independence of all <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors. The Board has established categorical standards consistent with the corporate governance standards of the NYSE to assist it in making
determinations of the independence of Board members. We have posted a copy of our Standards for Director Independence on our website at <I>www.sealedair.com</I>. These categorical standards require that, to be independent, a director may not have a
material relationship with Sealed Air. Even if a director meets all categorical standards for independence, the Board reviews other relationships with Sealed Air in order to conclude that each independent director has no material relationship with
Sealed Air either directly or indirectly. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">The Board has determined that the following director nominees are independent: Michael Chu,
Fran&ccedil;oise Colpron, Patrick Duff, Henry&nbsp;R. Keizer, Jacqueline&nbsp;B. Kosecoff, Harry A. Lawton III, Neil Lustig and Jerry&nbsp;R. Whitaker. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#12737c"><I><A NAME="toc685314_7"></A>Code of Conduct </I></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">We have a Code of Conduct applicable to all directors, officers and
employees of Sealed Air and its subsidiaries. We also have a supplemental Code of Ethics for Senior Financial Executives that applies to our Chief Executive Officer or CEO, Chief Financial Officer or CFO, Controller, Treasurer and all other
employees performing similar functions. We have posted the Code of Conduct and the Code of Ethics for Senior Financial Executives on our website at <I>www.sealedair.com</I>. We will post any amendments to the Code of Conduct and the Code of Ethics
for Senior Financial Executives on our website. In accordance with the requirements of the SEC and the NYSE, we will also post waivers applicable to any of our officers or directors from provisions of the Code of Conduct or the Code of Ethics for
Senior Financial Executives on our website. We have not granted any such waivers to date. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><I><A NAME="toc685314_8"></A>Board Oversight of
Risk </I></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">The Board of Directors is actively involved in oversight of risks that could affect Sealed Air. The Board has delegated oversight
of certain specific risk areas to Committees of the Board. For example, the Audit Committee oversees cybersecurity risk management as well as our major financial risk exposures and the steps we have taken to monitor and control such exposures, while
the Organization and Compensation Committee considers risks arising in connection with the design of the Company&#146;s compensation programs and succession planning. The risk oversight responsibility of each Board Committee is described in its
committee charter available at <I>www.sealedair.com</I>. The Board as a whole, however, is responsible for oversight of our risk management processes and our enterprise risk management program. The Board regularly discusses risk management with
management and among the directors during meetings. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">14 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Cybersecurity risk oversight is a top priority for the Board. While the Board has delegated the
specific responsibility of cybersecurity risk oversight to the Audit Committee, the Board is actively involved in overseeing cybersecurity risk management, both through presentations given by members of management during Board meetings as well as
regular reports from the Audit Committee on its cybersecurity risk oversight activities. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><I><A NAME="toc685314_9"></A>Communicating with
Directors </I></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Stockholders and other interested parties may communicate directly with the
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-management</FONT> directors of the Board of Directors by writing to <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Management</FONT> Directors, c/o Corporate Secretary, at Sealed Air Corporation, 2415&nbsp;Cascade Pointe
Boulevard, Charlotte, North Carolina 28208, or by sending an email to <I>directors@sealedair.com</I>. In either case, the Chairman of the Board will be notified of all such correspondence as appropriate and will communicate with the other directors
as appropriate about the correspondence. We have posted information on how to communicate with the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-management</FONT> directors on our website at <I>www.sealedair.com</I>. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><I><A NAME="toc685314_10"></A>Board Leadership Structure </I></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Jerry R. Whitaker was elected as the Chairman of the Board of Directors on May&nbsp;17, 2018. The Chairman presides at meetings of the Board at which he
or she is present and leads the Board in fulfilling its responsibilities as specified in the Bylaws. The Chairman has the right to call special and emergency meetings. The Chairman serves as the liaison for interested parties who request direct
communications with the Board. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Notwithstanding the appointment of a Chairman, the Board considers all of its members responsible and accountable
for oversight and guidance of its activities. All directors have the opportunity to request items to be included on the agendas of upcoming meetings. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">The Board believes having an independent Chairman is beneficial in that it ensures that management is subject to independent and objective oversight and
the independent directors have an active voice in the governance of Sealed Air. The leadership structure is reviewed annually as part of the Board&#146;s self-assessment process, and changes may be made in the future to reflect the Board&#146;s
composition as well as our needs and circumstances. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#12737c"><I><A NAME="toc685314_11"></A>Board of Directors Overview </I></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Under our Bylaws and the Delaware General Corporation Law, our business and affairs are managed by or under the direction of the Board of Directors,
which delegates some of its responsibilities to its Committees. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">The Board generally holds five regular meetings per year and meets on other
occasions when circumstances require. Directors spend additional time preparing for Board and Committee meetings, and we may call upon directors for advice between meetings. We encourage our directors to attend director education programs. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">The Corporate Governance Guidelines adopted by the Board provide that the Board will meet regularly in executive session without management in
attendance. The Chairman of the Board presides at each executive session. The Chairman&#146;s designee or the chair of the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee serves as the presiding director if the Chairman of the Board is unable to
serve. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">Under the Corporate Governance Guidelines, we expect directors to regularly attend meetings of the Board and of all Committees on which they
serve and to review the materials sent to them in advance </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right">15 </P>

</DIV></Center>

consent, and held six executive sessions and seven executive sessions with only independent directors. Each current director who served during 2018 participated in at least 90% of the aggregate number of meetings of the Board during 2018. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">The Board maintains an Audit Committee, a Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee, and an Organization and Compensation Committee. The members of
these Committees consist only of independent directors. The Board has adopted charters for each of the Committees, which are reviewed annually by the Committees and the Board. The Committee charters are available on our website at
<I>www.sealedair.com</I>. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="justify">We have a strong commitment to diversity of background and experience among our directors, as described below under

Sealed Air Corporation, 2415&nbsp;Cascade Pointe Boulevard, Charlotte, North Carolina 28208, along with additional required information about the nominee and the stockholder making the recommendation. Information on qualifications for nominations to
the Board and procedures for stockholder nominations to the Board is included below under &#147;Proposal&nbsp;1. Election of Directors&#151;Director Qualifications&#148; and&nbsp;&#147;&#151;Identifying and Evaluating Nominees for Directors.&#148;
